%reduceonerror should be in the .mly file?

Should we keep the "Ill-formed ..." headers? or remove them all?

When we say "if this list is complete..."
we should also say that if it is not complete, then it can
be continued with a comma, etc.
Same thing for attribute_specifier_list, declarator.

When a nonempty list is expected, there can be hesitation: should we say "an
element is expected", or "a nonempty list is expected"?

Revoir tous les messages d'erreur pour voir où $i peut servir.

If the problematic token is a name, it could have been mis-classified;
  show how it was classified.

Vérifier un par un les résultats de la comparaison ccomp/gcc/clang.

Revoir toutes les catégories syntaxiques et en donner des exemples.
  (Qui peuvent être ajoutés automatiquement?)
List of syntatic categories that appear in error messages:
  _Alignas qualifier
  assembly operand
  attribute specifier
  clobbered resource (another name for string_literal)
  coumpound literal
  enumerator
  enumeration specifier
  expression
  gcc attribute
  initializer
  list of declarators (possibly empty, but usually non-empty; comma-separated);
  list of expressions (argument_expression_list) (possibly empty; comma-separated)
  list of init declarators (non-empty; comma-separated)
  list of initializers
  list of inputs (possibly empty; comma-separated) (in asm statements)
  list of outputs (possibly empty; comma-separated) (in asm statements)
  list of parameter declarations (parameter_list, parameter_type_list) (possibly empty; comma-separated)
  list of pointers (possibly empty; whitespace-separated)
  struct declaration (could be baptized "declaration of a struct or union member"?)
  struct or union specifier
  type cast
  type name

